# Deterministic LLM Output Contract

Treat LLM output structure as a pipeline contract, not a cosmetic cleanup step.

## Core policy

- Never patch run artifacts under `runs/` to make outputs look clean.
- Fix generation-time logic in `src/` so reruns produce correct structure by default.
- Prefer fail-fast validation over silent post-hoc rewriting.

## Required implementation pattern

- Every phase that consumes LLM text must define explicit expected structure.
- Prompts must require exact labeled blocks or schema-constrained fields.
- Add deterministic sanitization only for bounded mechanical fixes (whitespace, marker cleanup, token normalization).
- If required structure is missing, trigger a deterministic repair pass at source or fail the gate.
- Keep one canonical source of truth for counts/facts used across manuscript, protocol, and exports.

## Quality gates and tests

- Add/maintain strict contract checks for headings, abstract fields, citation tokens, placeholders, and cross-artifact consistency.
- Extend unit tests for each new structural contract and each previous regression.
- A fix is complete only when rerun outputs pass contracts without manual artifact edits.

